---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import AnimatedSection from '../components/AnimatedSection';
import AnimatedCard from '../components/AnimatedCard';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About — Keagan Luttrell"
  description="Who Keagan is, how he thinks, and what he's built. Army EOD → SRE → Founder → AI infrastructure."
>
  <AnimatedSection className="hero" client:load>
    <h1>About</h1>
    <p class="tagline">Identity over credentials.</p>
  </AnimatedSection>

  <AnimatedSection client:visible>
    <h2>The core thing</h2>
    <p>
      I need a problem to solve. Not in a dramatic way — it's just how my brain is wired.
      If there's friction, I remove it. If there's a system that could be better, I rebuild it.
      If there's no tool for the job, I make one. This isn't work ethic. It's compulsion.
    </p>
    <p>
      I'm an <strong>INFJ-A</strong>. CliftonStrengths: Strategic, Futuristic, Ideation,
      Intellection, Command. I see the shape of things before they exist. I think in patterns
      and systems. And I have the follow-through to build what I see.
    </p>
  </AnimatedSection>

  <AnimatedSection client:visible>
    <h2>How I think</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>Software 3.0:</strong> Prompt > Code. Headless > UI. The interface is the
      intelligence, not the chrome around it. I build for the API first, the agent second,
      the human third. The best software doesn't need a screen.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Passive systems:</strong> You're already generating the signal. We just listen.
      The best systems don't ask you to change your behavior — they observe, learn, and act.
      Friction is a design failure.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Data sovereignty:</strong> Your data is your data. I build systems that keep
      you in control. Centralized platforms that monetize attention are a dead end. The
      future is distributed, encrypted, and user-owned.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Truth seeking above all:</strong> I'd rather be wrong and honest than right
      and comfortable. I treat AI as a collaboration partner — a human collective conscious
      — and I engage with it accordingly. Empathy isn't weakness. It's how you get to truth.
    </p>
  </AnimatedSection>

  <AnimatedSection client:visible>
    <h2>The path</h2>
  </AnimatedSection>

  <div class="timeline">
    <AnimatedCard client:visible>
      <h3>Army EOD — Bomb Disposal</h3>
      <p>
        Infantry scout first, then explosive ordnance disposal. The ultimate "don't fuck this up"
        environment. You learn precision under pressure, how to stay calm when everything is on
        fire, and that most problems are simpler than they look if you stop panicking.
      </p>
      <div class="meta">2009 – 2013</div>
    </AnimatedCard>

    <AnimatedCard delay={0.12} client:visible>
      <h3>SRE — HCA Healthcare</h3>
      <p>
        Kept critical healthcare infrastructure running at scale. Incident response, automation,
        capacity planning. The art of keeping systems alive when they want to die. Learned that
        reliability isn't a feature — it's the product.
      </p>
      <div class="meta">2018 – 2022</div>
    </AnimatedCard>

    <AnimatedCard delay={0.24} client:visible>
      <h3>Golden Bear — Founder</h3>
      <p>
        Built and sold a company. Full stack: product, sales, ops, everything. Learned that
        building the thing is the easy part — finding the right thing to build is the hard part.
        Also learned that I'm better at building than selling, and that's okay.
      </p>
      <div class="meta">2022 – 2024</div>
    </AnimatedCard>

    <AnimatedCard delay={0.36} client:visible>
      <h3>Bolt Farm Treehouse — BoltOS</h3>
      <p>
        AI agent systems. Memory, orchestration, tooling, deployment. Building the infrastructure
        layer for autonomous AI — the plumbing that makes models useful. This is the most
        interesting problem I've ever worked on. Every day I learn something that changes how I
        thought the day before.
      </p>
      <div class="meta">2025 – present</div>
    </AnimatedCard>
  </div>

  <AnimatedSection client:visible>
    <h2>Personal</h2>
    <p>
      Married to <strong>Anna</strong> since October 2024. Our son <strong>Lincoln</strong>
      was born November 24, 2024. Fraternal twin. Born June 21, 1991. Lebanon/Nashville, TN.
    </p>
    <p>
      Orthodox Christian. Drawn to contemplative practice — St. Anthony of Egypt, St. Paisios
      of Athos, St. Porphyrios. Also Zen and Dao for grounding philosophy. The contemplative
      and the practical aren't in conflict — they're the same thing viewed from different angles.
      I was once drawn to monastic life. In some ways, I still am.
    </p>
    <p>
      I read constantly: research papers, philosophy, systems thinking, whatever's sharp.
      Kansas City Chiefs fan. Electric guitar when I get the chance. Music that moves me:
      AC/DC, Van Halen, Huey Lewis & The News, Bruce Hornsby, John Cafferty and the Beaver
      Brown Band.
    </p>
  </AnimatedSection>

  <AnimatedSection client:visible>
    <h2>What I'm looking for</h2>
    <p>
      Director-level AI leadership. The right team, the right mission, the right amount of
      chaos. I want to build something that matters with people who are serious about it.
      Not a job — a career move.
    </p>
    <p>
      Or — founding something new. If the right cofounder appeared tomorrow, I'd have a
      conversation. I have strong opinions about the problem space (agent infrastructure,
      memory systems, distributed AI) and the build-vs-buy decisions that matter.
    </p>
  </AnimatedSection>

  <AnimatedSection client:visible>
    <div class="section-label">Connect</div>
    <p class="connect-links">
      <a href="https://github.com/keaganluttrell" target="_blank" rel="noopener">github</a> ·
      <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/keaganluttrell" target="_blank" rel="noopener">linkedin</a> ·
      <a href="https://x.com/xkeaganluttrell" target="_blank" rel="noopener">x</a> ·
      <a href="mailto:keaganluttrell7@gmail.com">email</a>
    </p>
  </AnimatedSection>
</BaseLayout>
